Language name: BETE
Language number: 4144
Alternate names: 
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, Kru
Comments: Werle and Gbalehi analyze Bete as having four 
level tones. Bete has a vowel harmony system (actually 
based on tongue root position) in which the lowered high 
and lower mid vowels do not combine with fully high or 
higher mid vowels; /a/ is neutral to vowel harmony.
Sources: 

Werle, J-M. and Gbalehi, D.J. 1976. Phonologie et 
morphonologie du Bete de la Region de Guiberoua. Institut 
de Linguistique Appliquee, Universite d'Abidjan.